EXCLUSIVE: Michelle Obama Reads From Her Forthcoming Memoir 'Becoming'Enlarge this image toggle caption Chuck Kennedy for NPR Chuck Kennedy for NPRMichelle Obama's new memoir Becoming, about her life from childhood through the White House years, comes out Tuesday.
NPR was provided an exclusive listen Monday to two sections of the audio book, read by Obama herself.
Michelle Obama on Princeton 4:27In the first, Obama focuses on her impressions of Princeton, being a minority there, and college life.
"The hope was that all of us would mingle in heterogeneous harmony," she says of the university's vision for the various races.
